{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"69cb1d48-27ec-4132-b77b-d07fc35a554d","content":"Use **`dotnet test`**, not `dotnet run`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package integrates with the Microsoft Testing Platform. When you run:\n\n```\ndotnet test\n```\n\nwith the `TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1` environment variable set, the test host stays alive and watches for file changes, re-running affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet run` won't work here because this is a test project (`IsPackable=false`, no entry point for a regular app). Hot reload for tests is driven through the testing platform, which `dotnet test` invokes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dc2706b7-e290-467a-a93f-af13b345f6b0","outputTokens":145,"requestId":"B450:3577AF:DBF263:E9F75A:6A044D5E"},"id":"70ca579d-0a04-4e4b-9044-0c762c6a84f4","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:32.631Z","parentId":"4aefd3c7-e544-423c-9fc2-2a68a987d1fa"}
